HEADWORD: Endodermis
<hw>En`do*der"mis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Endoderm</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A layer of cells
forming a kind of cuticle inside of the proper cortical layer, or
surrounding an individual fibrovascular bundle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

